tf:TrustInteroperabilityProfileReference.tf:Name: NIST 800-63 Credential Verification Profile for all LOAs
tf:TrustInteroperabilityProfileReference.tf:Description: This Trust Interoperability Profile specifies NIST 800-63 requirements on credential verification services provided by CSPs, for LOAs 1 - 4.

tf:TrustInteroperabilityProfileReference.tf:Name: NIST 800-63 LOA 2 Renewal and Re-Issuance Profile

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Revocation of Tokens and Credentials Within 72 Hours
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for the revocation of tokens and credentials within 72 hours of a CSP becoming notified of a compromise.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Token and Credential Provenance Record Retention
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for maintaining token and credential provenance records.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Policies for Token and Credential Renewal and Re-Issuance
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for establishing policies for token and credential renewal and re-issuance.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Basic Renewal and Re-Issuance of Tokens and Credentials
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers basic requirements for token and credential renewal and re-issuance, by Credential Service Providers (CSPs).

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Expiration of Tokens and Credentials With Grace Periods
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for the expiration, with grace periods, of tokens and credentials.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Renewal and Re-Issuance of Passwords
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for the renewal and re-issuance of passwords for their subscribers.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Mitigation of Basic Subscriber Authentication Threats
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for mitigating threats of online guessing, replay, eavesdropping, and session hijacking to authentication processes.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Subscriber Authentication Process
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers basic requirements for subscriber authentication, done by Credential Service Providers (CSPs).

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Weak Mitigation of Subscriber Authentication MITM Threats
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers requirements on Credential Service Providers (CSPs) for weak resistance of the man-in-the-middle threat to authentication processes.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Use of Approved Cryptography for Protection of Subscriber Authentication Session Data
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers the use of approved cryptography, by Credential Service Providers (CSPs), for protecting session data during authentication processes.

tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Name: Use of Multi-Factor Subscriber Authentication
tf:TrustmarkDefinitionReference.tf:Description: This Trustmark Definition covers the use of multi-factor authentication, by Credential Service Providers (CSPs), in authentication processes.

tf:TrustInteroperabilityProfile.tf:TrustExpression: TD_1 AND TD_2 AND TD_3 AND TD_4 AND TD_5
